/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:725:1. The frame contract's `plan_version` increment triggers a snapshot of the prior plan's wave assignments; the dashboard caches the last accepted plan in `lastGoodPlan`.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:940:Plan and state files mutate independently and may be observed mid-write. To prevent mixed-frame truth, the dashboard treats every render as a paired snapshot.
/Users/darkbit1001/workspace/waveplan-mcp/docs/specs/2026-04-28-plan-state-dashboard-design.md:1086:Each component reads from a shared `ComparedView`. No component fetches independently; the polling layer publishes new `ComparedView` snapshots.
